ABOUT KATALON
Founded in 2016, Katalon is the leading provider of a modern, comprehensive quality management platform. Katalon Platform enables quality assurance, DevOps, and software teams of any size to deliver world-class customer experiences faster, easier, and more efficiently.
Since its first launch, Katalon has experienced tremendous growth, serving more than 100,000 users across 30,000 teams of all shapes & sizes, many of which are in the Fortune Global 500, such as PwC, KMPG, Abbott, Standard Chartered, etc. Katalon is recognized as a top automation tool by prestigious review sites, such as Gartner, Capterra, and IT Central Station.
Katalon is headquartered in Atlanta, GA. For more info about Katalon, please visit
 ABOUT POSITION
Calling all passionate Associate Technical Product Managers! If you thrive in fast-paced environments and are eager to collaborate with both product and engineering teams to drive innovation, then this role is for you.
Here's a snapshot of what you'll be doing:
Gather, analyze, and create high-level requirements;
Participate in the product prototyping process, interface mock-up, wireframe, and GUI creation in an Agile environment;
Analyze market trends and perform competitor analysis;
Share the business value with the development team, so they understand the intent behind the new feature, release, or product
Work with the assigned Product Managers to define the product roadmap and vision;
Prioritize features by ranking them against the strategic goals and initiatives to ensure the delivery of the product, including managing dependencies in and across releases to complete release phases and milestones;
Coordinating all of the activities required to bring the product to market. This involves bridging gaps between different functions within the company and aligning all of the teams involved (e.g: Marketing, Sales & Sucess, Customer Support, others);
Determine which ideas should be promoted into features to push the product strategy forward;
Ensure that feedback and requests are seamlessly integrated into the product planning and development processes.

