Are you passionate about ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of cutting-edge systems? Do you thrive in environments driven by innovation in AI-driven software development? Join Renn Labs, where your enthusiasm meets high-energy, collaborative, and forward-thinking tech innovation. We're on the lookout for a skilled QA/QC Engineer to play a key role in enhancing the technological excellence of our innovative AI applications. This is more than a job – it's a chance to be at the forefront of technological advancement with a team that values creativity and innovation.
 The QA/QC Engineer is a crucial role, responsible for working closely with product managers, designers, and engineers to establish, enforce and implement quality assurance standards and practices. This position is central to our software product development, ensuring innovation is matched with exceptional quality and reliability.
Ready to elevate your value to new heights and redefine the future? Uplift your Test Engineering journey with Renn Labs today.
 IN DETAIL, YOUR SUCCESS IN THIS JOB WILL BE
  Effectively developing and executing detailed test plans and test cases for both new features and regression testing, balancing manual and automated testing strategies to ensure comprehensive coverage;
Proactively working within the software engineers to identify potential issues / bugs early in the development cycle, aiming to prevent defects before deployment;
Efficiently implementing and maintaining automated tests within our CI/CD pipeline, contributing to streamlined and reliable testing processes.
Continuously engaging in learning to stay updated with the latest QA technologies and practices, applying this knowledge to systematically improve our testing framework;
Diligently supporting the development of testing standards and procedures to ensure continuous improvement in quality and efficiency across projects;
Thoroughly assisting in troubleshooting and resolving defects, providing detailed documentation and feedback to the development team to ensure timely resolutions;
Actively participating in agile development processes, including inceptions, planning, daily check-ins, reviews and retros, contributing a quality perspective to each phase with constructive insights;
Promptly comprehend the business flow and logic for each product to seamlessly transition across diverse projects while maintaining constant work effectiveness. This entails quickly understanding the unique requirements and challenges of each project to ensure quality assurance practices are effectively adapted and applied;
Timely and efficiently  troubleshooting and resolving any obstacles relating to the job.

